cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the task of learning cell-level visual representation in histopathology images using generative adversarial networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new formulation of loss and uses unsupervised learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of generative adversarial networks also indicates a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with histopathology image analysis, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
